CUa7Su4KebKHs_VwPQ9Esa2EyYhA4MqyA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1000;s:6:"height";i:1000;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/669980882059832003/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:59:{i:0;s:135:"Having your garage door light blink continuously is not only annoying its also a sign that there is something wrong with the mechanism.";i:1;s:68:"There are several reasons why your garage door opener is doing this.";i:2;s:119:"However the two most common reasons include a problem with the lock button and malfunctioning safety reversing sensors.";i:3;s:106:"Why is my garage door light flashing there are a few reasons why your garage door light might be flashing.";i:4;s:77:"Know that there is no need to panic or be too annoyed with that flashing yet.";i:5;s:132:"Modern garage door openers include technology that alerts us when theyre running into a problem similar to the alerts from our cars.";i:6;s:82:"The light from the opener blinks 10 times to warn you about misaligned photo eyes.";i:7;s:128:"To fix this issue first locate the two photo eyes attached to your garage door and clean the lens using a soft microfiber cloth.";i:8;s:101:"Loosen the wing nut holding up the photo eye and adjust them until both sensors are properly aligned.";i:9;s:150:"If you try to open your door using a remote while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door light will begin blinking continuously.";i:10;s:83:"The locking feature is meant to prevent garage door remotes from opening your door.";i:11;s:19:"Only the button on.";i:12;s:122:"Four flashes is the most common reason your opener lights may be flashing is because of your sensor eyes being misaligned.";i:13;s:125:"If an object has misaligned your sensor eyes then it breaks the electronic beam preventing the garage door to close properly.";i:14;s:44:"The door will stop and reverse back upwards.";i:15;s:81:"If the light or display is off check the garage door opener motor unit for power.";i:16;s:195:"The first thing you ll want to do when your garage door light is blinking is to check to see if the lock button sometimes referred to as the vacation button is turned on and if it is turn it off.";i:17;s:63:"Sonoff Garage Door Opener Garage Door Opener Garage Doors Door.";i:18;s:54:"Simply so why is my garage door opener light flashing.";i:19;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:20;s:96:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor wiring also cause the opener lights to blink 10 times.";i:21;s:107:"The safety sensors use an invisible beam of infrared light to detect obstructions in the garage doors path.";i:22;s:132:"If the overhead light is flashing you might have a problem with the safety sensors on either side of the garage door near the floor.";i:23;s:108:"Either something is blocking their view of each other or their alignment is off or a wire to one is damaged.";i:24;s:104:"If the opener does not receive the right signal from the sensors it will not allow the door to close as.";i:25;s:102:"Whether or not you have a garage door with a yellow light is determined by the brand of door you have.";i:26;s:63:"Craftsman Chamberlain and Liftmaster garage doors all have one.";i:27;s:92:"Your garage doors transmitter is linked to the yellow light and it should be on at all time.";i:28;s:80:"If its not then you should fix it as it may indicate an issue with your sensors.";i:29;s:141:"The garage door opener flashing wall button is completely different from photo-cell LED light being out or the motor head LED light flashing.";i:30;s:197:"The constantly flashing wall button simply means that the door was either put into lock-out mode by someone using the wall panel control or for some reason it defaulted into lock-out mode in error.";i:31;s:136:"If you see the orange light on the garage door sensor either flashing or is totally off this means that the sensor is losing the wiring.";i:32;s:164:"The purpose of the safety sensors located on the bottom corners of your garage door is to automatically reverse your door if they detect motion underneath the door.";i:33;s:114:"If the opener cannot detect that the safety sensors are properly working or connected then the opener lights will.";i:34;s:72:"Your garage door opener is programmed with self-diagnostic capabilities.";i:35;s:149:"The diagnostic LED light next to the learn button will flash a number of times then pause before repeating signifying it has found a potential issue.";i:36;s:80:"I have the traditional two light at the left and at the right of my garage door.";i:37;s:102:"The are on the same circuit with the porch light that has a PIR sensor turns on when move is detected.";i:38;s:70:"So it is power source--switch--Porch light--first light--second light.";i:39;s:68:"Check for a blinking light on the multi-function door control panel.";i:40;s:75:"If the light is blinking push the LOCK button to turn off the lock feature.";i:41;s:123:"Press and hold the LOCK button for 2 seconds then the LED will glow solid indicating the lock feature has been deactivated.";i:42;s:57:"Garage door sensors work using an infrared beam of light.";i:43;s:38:"Each sensor will usually have a light.";i:44;s:196:"One will have a green light used to show that the units are powered up and the other will have a red light to show that theres no obstruction between the sensors and that theyre seeing each other.";i:45;s:63:"Garage Door Opener Lights Flash and the Garage Door Wont Close.";i:46;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:47;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:48;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:49;s:139:"If your garage door opener wont open and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:50;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:51;s:49:"Garage Door Opener Flashing Led Light Not Moving.";i:52;s:47:"Garage Opener Light Blinking A Troubleshooting.";i:53;s:54:"The Light On One Of Safety Eye Sensors My Garage Door.";i:54;s:53:"Troubleshooting A Garage Door That Won T Close Chion.";i:55;s:61:"Garage Door Won T Close Safety Sensor Troubleshooting Lights.";i:56;s:25:"High Sd Fabric Doors 993.";i:57;s:176:"If your garage door opener is beeping every 30 seconds and you notice a red or orange light flashing alongside it then it means that your battery is out or well on its way out.";i:58;s:131:"Keep in mind that this is not the case with all garage door models- some have backup batteries or rechargeable batteries installed.";}}